}}As of the 2020 census, there were 785 people, 395 housing units, and 394 families in the CDP. There were 683 [[White Americans|White]] people,3 [[African Americans]], 15 Native Americans, 17 [[Asian Americans|Asians]], 6 people from some other race, and 61 people from two or more races. 334 people were from [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Glasgow_CDP;_Oregon?g=160XX00US4129100 |access-date=2023-05-25 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry in Glasgow was 19.4% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 16.9% [[German Americans|German]], 6.8% [[English Americans|English]], 5.7% [[Italian Americans|Italian]], 3.8% [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]], and 3.4% [[Polish Americans|Polish]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 57.3 years old. 31.3% of the population were older than 65, with 18.0% between the ages of 65 and 74, 12.0% between the ages of 75 and 84, and 1.4% 85 or older.<ref name=":0" />{{clear left}}

